stylometry: Bayes' Therom helps to make decisions in a decision tree model after new information is introduced.  This is so important because very rarely are business problems cut and dry, this allows some wiggle room if new information is introduced.  The company can still get a great answer because of Bayes' Therom. Posterior probabilities are determined by taking the prior information and adding it with the new information.  We need them because as said before, things change and problems must be adjusted. Posterior probabilities are important because it is including the information from the past, with the current new information, to make the best possible decision that it can with this change.
